], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_festivals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_festivals\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some organizers\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 288}, {\"ngram\": \"depictBacchanalia\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Throughout history, Bacchanalia has involved dancing, singing, and revelry, focused on the worship of Dionysus, the Olympian god revered in Greco-Roman religion as the deity of nature, fertility, vegetation, wine, and ecstasy.\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 409, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bacchanalia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bacchanalia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bacchanalia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bacchanalia\"}, {\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.775516841025206e-48, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 505, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twelve_Olympians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympian god\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twelve_Olympians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twelve_Olympians\"}, {\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greco-Roman_world\", \"score\": 0.9999999733045118, \"rank\": 2.447704168811125e-08, \"text\": \"Greco-Roman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greco-Roman_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greco-Roman_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"dancing\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 441}, {\"ngram\": \"singing\", \"from\": 443, 