om\": 4117, \"to\": 4125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No serious historian disputes that Western civilization has been deeply influenced by Christian morals for millennia.\", \"from\": 4134, \"to\": 4251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4169, \"end\": 4189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_culture\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8343463353152856e-14, \"text\": \"Western civilization\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_culture\"}, {\"begin\": 4220, \"end\": 4229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.556820554260298e-16, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No serious historian disputes\", \"from\": 4134, \"to\": 4163}, {\"ngram\": \"millennia\", \"from\": 4241, \"to\": 4250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Larry W. Hurtado argued in his2017 bookthat since the first century, Jesus has been depicted as a\\\"destroyer of the gods.\\\"\", \"from\": 4252, \"to\": 4373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4321, \"end\": 4326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999954543455, \"rank\": 4.545687030685662e-09, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Larry W. Hurtado\", \"from\": 4252, \"to\": 4268}, {\"ngram\": \"his2017\", \"from\": 4279, \"to\": 4286}, {\"ngram\": \"the first century\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4319}, {\"ngram\": \"a\\\"destroyer\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4359}, {\"ngram\": \"the gods\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hurtado illustrates how Jesus' movement introduced a distinctive religious identity with ethical principles that set it apart from Greek religions.\", 