\"InThe Will to Power,he went even further to add I have declared war on the anemic Christian ideal\\u2026, not with the aim of destroying it but only of putting an end to its tyranny and clearing the way for new ideals, formore robust ideals.\", \"from\": 5501, \"to\": 5737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5584, \"end\": 5593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.556820554260298e-16, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Power\", \"from\": 5515, \"to\": 5520}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5568}, {\"ngram\": \"the aim\", \"from\": 5610, \"to\": 5617}, {\"ngram\": \"an end\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5661}, {\"ngram\": \"its tyranny\", \"from\": 5665, \"to\": 5676}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 5690, \"to\": 5697}, {\"ngram\": \"new ideals\", \"from\": 5702, \"to\": 5712}, {\"ngram\": \"formore robust ideals\", \"from\": 5714, \"to\": 5735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"English philosopher Frederick Copleston concurred that Dionysus, for Nietzsche, symbolizes the unbridled stream of life itself, breaking down all barriers and disregarding all restraints.\", \"from\": 5739, \"to\": 5927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5739, \"end\": 5746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"score\": 0.9999906193719441, \"rank\": 6.95808909041657e-06, \"text\": \"English\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\"}, {\"begin\": 5759, \"end\": 5778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Copleston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Frederick Copleston\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Copleston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederi